1
00:02:15,040 --> 00:02:17,800
{\an8}My name is Bella. You can call me Bell.

2
00:02:19,680 --> 00:02:21,240
{\an8}I'm Anapat.

3
00:02:27,280 --> 00:02:29,520
{\an8}Hello, Mr. Thee. Welcome.

4
00:02:36,320 --> 00:02:38,520
{\an8}I've gone over the contract with Mr. Thee.

5
00:02:38,600 --> 00:02:41,320
A hotel won't be able to make much profit.

6
00:02:45,760 --> 00:02:49,000
Because what I'll get
is more than just a profit.

7
00:02:51,280 --> 00:02:53,800
I'll get to do
what I've been longing to do.

8
00:02:58,560 --> 00:03:00,400
Enough about work.

9
00:03:00,480 --> 00:03:01,640
I need to rest my brain.

10
00:03:04,160 --> 00:03:05,200
Thank you.

11
00:03:51,080 --> 00:03:52,040
Yeah.

12
00:04:24,560 --> 00:04:25,480
Good.

13
00:04:25,560 --> 00:04:28,000
I wanted to talk to Joe about our kids.

14
00:05:30,840 --> 00:05:31,680
RECENTS - BELLA BELL

15
00:05:37,160 --> 00:05:38,520
- Hello.
- Bell!

16
00:05:39,360 --> 00:05:40,880
Hello.

17
00:05:45,160 --> 00:05:47,320
How's Thailand this time around?

18
00:05:48,200 --> 00:05:49,160
It's quite fun.

19
00:05:49,240 --> 00:05:53,000
The people here are smiley and sweet,
and there are tons of cool new spots.

20
00:05:54,640 --> 00:05:57,480
I just hope you won't find
anyone sweeter than Thee.

21
00:06:11,760 --> 00:06:14,200
There you go again with that nonsense.

22
00:06:16,800 --> 00:06:20,280
What you see as nonsense is my happiness.

23
00:06:21,200 --> 00:06:22,680
Is something the matter, Dad?

24
00:06:25,400 --> 00:06:28,360
I just wanted to tell you
to get ready to marry Thee.

25
00:06:28,880 --> 00:06:30,520
I've talked to his parents.

26
00:06:31,160 --> 00:06:33,240
Dad, I already told you,

27
00:06:33,320 --> 00:06:36,000
I've got nothing against marrying Thee,

28
00:06:37,040 --> 00:06:38,960
but just don't forget our promise,

29
00:06:40,160 --> 00:06:42,280
that you won't stop me
from doing what I love

30
00:06:42,880 --> 00:06:44,880
and that you'll stay out of my life.

31
00:06:47,200 --> 00:06:49,200
You're just as stubborn as your mother.

32
00:07:07,200 --> 00:07:09,960
Did you do what I asked, Pitak?

33
00:07:11,440 --> 00:07:12,400
Yes.

34
00:07:13,120 --> 00:07:15,120
Mr. Thee still doesn't know you're here.

35
00:07:15,200 --> 00:07:16,400
Good.

36
00:07:17,160 --> 00:07:19,000
I'm taking Bell to surprise him.

37
00:07:21,760 --> 00:07:23,240
Are you ready, Bell?

38
00:07:24,080 --> 00:07:24,920
Yes.

39
00:07:46,600 --> 00:07:48,760
Mr. Thee sure is nice.

40
00:07:49,280 --> 00:07:51,280
He gave us a nice room to stay,

41
00:07:51,360 --> 00:07:54,040
and he hosted this beach party for us.

42
00:07:54,120 --> 00:07:57,120
I'd better give him
the Best Husband award.

43
00:07:58,960 --> 00:08:01,920
Why don't you pray for it
in your next life?

44
00:08:02,000 --> 00:08:04,640
Because in this life,
Mook already bagged him.

45
00:08:05,720 --> 00:08:08,920
You're right! Mr. Thee
spoils Mook in every way.

46
00:08:09,000 --> 00:08:10,240
He clearly loves her a lot.

47
00:08:13,840 --> 00:08:15,840
I swear to do only good deeds.

48
00:08:16,600 --> 00:08:19,240
Please bless me with someone
good and caring in my next life.

49
00:08:19,760 --> 00:08:21,160
As for this life,

50
00:08:21,240 --> 00:08:23,600
I'll remember to pray for my enemies,

51
00:08:24,320 --> 00:08:26,440
so they can stop bugging me!

52
00:08:28,480 --> 00:08:30,360
Pray for the shrimp too.
He really needs it.

53
00:08:30,440 --> 00:08:32,200
- Calm down.
- "I'm so cooked!"

54
00:08:33,120 --> 00:08:33,960
- Auntie!
- Are you hungry?

55
00:08:34,039 --> 00:08:35,880
Are you hungry, Kongkwan?

56
00:08:36,400 --> 00:08:37,679
Auntie.

57
00:08:37,760 --> 00:08:39,919
- Yes, dear?
- You're here just in time.

58
00:08:40,000 --> 00:08:41,520
We're almost done grilling the seafood.

59
00:08:41,600 --> 00:08:42,840
Please have a seat.

60
00:08:42,919 --> 00:08:44,280
Can I help you with anything?

61
00:08:44,360 --> 00:08:45,560
No, Mom!

62
00:08:45,640 --> 00:08:48,000
You two can just wait over there.

63
00:08:48,080 --> 00:08:50,080
- Follow me.
- Please.

64
00:08:50,160 --> 00:08:52,080
- Yes.
- You look pretty.

65
00:08:52,160 --> 00:08:53,560
Thank you, Auntie.

66
00:08:53,640 --> 00:08:55,240
- You can sit there at the end.
- Thank you.

67
00:08:57,200 --> 00:08:59,840
Go ahead, Kongkwan. Up.

68
00:09:06,600 --> 00:09:08,400
- Look! You hungry?
- Where's Mook, though?

69
00:09:09,000 --> 00:09:13,280
Mook said she's inviting Mrs. Narin,
the CEO of the hotel, to join us.

70
00:09:13,360 --> 00:09:14,200
She'll be back soon.

71
00:09:14,280 --> 00:09:15,200
- Okay.
- Yeah.

72
00:09:16,240 --> 00:09:17,360
Doesn't it look delicious?

73
00:09:18,080 --> 00:09:20,000
It smells so good that I got hungry.

74
00:09:20,640 --> 00:09:22,040
Then don't hold back, okay?

75
00:09:22,640 --> 00:09:24,960
If it's not good, blame the chef.

76
00:09:26,680 --> 00:09:29,920
Please, Mrs. Narin, join us.

77
00:09:30,520 --> 00:09:32,760
It'll be fun. I promise.

78
00:09:34,200 --> 00:09:35,520
- Please?
- I don't know.

79
00:09:35,600 --> 00:09:37,600
I wanted you to meet my team too.

80
00:09:45,080 --> 00:09:46,040
Mr. Thee.

81
00:09:47,160 --> 00:09:49,320
I'm inviting Mrs. Narin to join our party.

82
00:09:54,080 --> 00:09:57,200
I don't want to bother him. I'd better go.

83
00:10:05,560 --> 00:10:06,640
Please feel free to join.

84
00:10:08,200 --> 00:10:09,920
We rarely get to eat together.

85
00:10:14,200 --> 00:10:16,160
Let's go, Mrs. Narin.

86
00:10:17,000 --> 00:10:18,280
Thank you. Let's go.

87
00:10:26,040 --> 00:10:26,920
You're here!

88
00:10:27,000 --> 00:10:28,040
- So many people!
- There they are.

89
00:10:28,560 --> 00:10:30,520
Kongkwan, look, they're here!

90
00:10:31,200 --> 00:10:32,160
Look!

91
00:10:34,400 --> 00:10:35,440
What's up, honey?

92
00:10:39,200 --> 00:10:41,400
This is Mrs. Narin, the owner here.

93
00:10:41,480 --> 00:10:43,120
- Good evening.
- Good evening.

94
00:10:43,200 --> 00:10:44,000
Good evening.

95
00:10:44,080 --> 00:10:46,080
Mrs. Narin, this is my team,
and that's my mother.

96
00:10:47,200 --> 00:10:48,960
- Nice to meet you.
- Likewise.

97
00:10:50,440 --> 00:10:51,640
Oh, and this is Kongkwan.

98
00:10:51,720 --> 00:10:53,040
She's my daughter.

99
00:10:53,120 --> 00:10:54,400
Oh, really?

100
00:10:54,480 --> 00:10:56,520
Kongkwan, say hello to Mrs. Narin.

101
00:10:57,120 --> 00:10:58,640
Hello, Aunt Narin.

102
00:10:59,880 --> 00:11:01,280
Hello, dear.

103
00:11:01,360 --> 00:11:02,520
Aren't you cute?

104
00:11:02,600 --> 00:11:04,480
My son's just as cute as you.

105
00:11:06,240 --> 00:11:08,040
You have a son too?

106
00:11:08,120 --> 00:11:09,120
Yes.

107
00:11:10,800 --> 00:11:12,240
Why don't you sit with me?

108
00:11:14,240 --> 00:11:15,640
- Come on.
- I see.

109
00:11:18,520 --> 00:11:21,360
ANAPAT

110
00:11:23,040 --> 00:11:25,040
Sorry, I have to take this.

111
00:11:25,120 --> 00:11:26,560
Please, go ahead.

112
00:11:27,640 --> 00:11:28,840
Please have a seat.

113
00:11:28,920 --> 00:11:31,240
Thank you. How's the food?

114
00:11:31,320 --> 00:11:32,360
It's very good!

115
00:11:32,440 --> 00:11:34,040
- Thank you.
- It's great. Thank you.

116
00:11:51,840 --> 00:11:53,040
<i>Where are you, Boss?</i>

117
00:11:53,560 --> 00:11:56,200
I'm almost there, Mook.
How's the location?

118
00:11:57,320 --> 00:11:59,720
The rooms and the ballrooms are good,

119
00:11:59,800 --> 00:12:02,320
but they'll need more decorations
to fit the concept.

120
00:12:02,840 --> 00:12:05,000
You should hurry.
The party's in full swing.

121
00:12:05,840 --> 00:12:07,600
Okay. I'll be right over.

122
00:12:07,680 --> 00:12:08,760
Okay. Drive safe.

123
00:12:18,960 --> 00:12:20,560
So Thee's here, Aunt Anna?

124
00:12:20,640 --> 00:12:21,840
They're all here.

125
00:12:25,320 --> 00:12:26,840
There are others too, Mr. Pitak?

126
00:12:26,920 --> 00:12:27,960
Yes.

127
00:12:28,480 --> 00:12:29,600
Who are they?

128
00:12:29,680 --> 00:12:32,760
It's a long story, Ms. Bell.
There's nothing we can do now.

129
00:12:33,480 --> 00:12:34,640
You'd better hurry.

130
00:12:37,960 --> 00:12:39,560
- And drive me to work.
- Oh.

131
00:12:42,800 --> 00:12:43,720
Mr. Thee,

132
00:12:43,800 --> 00:12:47,320
is Mr. Pitak not here with you?
Why haven't I seen him?

133
00:12:48,320 --> 00:12:51,040
He said he had an important event
and he couldn't come.

134
00:12:51,560 --> 00:12:55,360
But he actually handled
this party and our accommodation.

135
00:12:58,840 --> 00:13:01,400
You even noticed Mr. Pitak's not here.

136
00:13:01,480 --> 00:13:05,040
How come you never care about me as much?

137
00:13:06,000 --> 00:13:07,080
Sorry about that.

138
00:13:09,040 --> 00:13:12,640
Mook sure is taking her time
with that call.

139
00:13:14,360 --> 00:13:15,360
Right?

140
00:13:21,320 --> 00:13:23,800
That's Mr. Pitak!
I thought he had an event?

141
00:13:28,320 --> 00:13:29,400
Mom.

142
00:13:39,880 --> 00:13:42,040
Everyone, this is my mother.

143
00:13:42,960 --> 00:13:45,040
- Good evening.
- Good evening.

144
00:13:46,400 --> 00:13:47,640
Good evening.

145
00:13:49,040 --> 00:13:51,920
I heard Thee was hosting
a party for his team,

146
00:13:52,520 --> 00:13:54,600
so I wanted to greet all of you.

147
00:13:58,200 --> 00:14:01,080
This is Bell, Thee's fiancée.

148
00:14:14,600 --> 00:14:15,440
Mook.

149
00:14:17,600 --> 00:14:18,640
Mommy.

150
00:14:22,280 --> 00:14:23,240
Come.

151
00:14:26,520 --> 00:14:28,600
I take it you're Ms. Veluree.

152
00:14:28,680 --> 00:14:31,480
Thee told me you work with him

153
00:14:31,560 --> 00:14:33,400
and you're very talented.

154
00:14:35,240 --> 00:14:37,480
You look pretty young.

155
00:14:37,560 --> 00:14:41,000
It's hard to believe
your daughter's this big already.

156
00:14:43,080 --> 00:14:44,720
Nice to meet you.

157
00:14:47,160 --> 00:14:48,120
Hello.

158
00:14:58,200 --> 00:14:59,520
I should go to bed.

159
00:15:00,760 --> 00:15:01,600
Sure.

160
00:15:02,920 --> 00:15:05,360
I usually don't stay up late.

161
00:15:11,560 --> 00:15:12,520
Mook,

162
00:15:13,160 --> 00:15:14,240
please walk me.

163
00:15:15,640 --> 00:15:16,640
Let's go.

164
00:15:17,360 --> 00:15:19,600
But I don't want to go yet, Grandma.

165
00:15:25,800 --> 00:15:27,880
Can I stay with Thee?

166
00:15:33,880 --> 00:15:34,960
Kongkwan,

167
00:15:35,920 --> 00:15:37,240
listen to Mommy, okay?

168
00:15:38,400 --> 00:15:40,040
You promised me, remember?

169
00:15:45,600 --> 00:15:46,440
Let's go, honey.

170
00:15:57,800 --> 00:15:58,760
Thee!

171
00:15:58,840 --> 00:16:00,240
Aunt Anna.

172
00:16:02,440 --> 00:16:05,280
What's all this about? Who's that woman?

173
00:16:08,640 --> 00:16:11,560
If you don't answer me,
I'll go tell my dad.

174
00:16:12,560 --> 00:16:14,320
Bell, wait!

175
00:16:14,920 --> 00:16:16,000
Bell!

176
00:16:17,560 --> 00:16:18,440
Bell!

177
00:16:29,000 --> 00:16:32,160
Sorry for killing the mood.

178
00:16:34,160 --> 00:16:35,080
It's okay.

179
00:16:39,000 --> 00:16:41,560
Well then, please enjoy.

180
00:16:41,640 --> 00:16:44,240
- Okay, thank you.
- Good night.

181
00:16:49,600 --> 00:16:50,760
What on earth is going on?

182
00:16:51,440 --> 00:16:53,240
This is real, right?

183
00:16:53,760 --> 00:16:55,120
Am I dreaming?

184
00:16:55,640 --> 00:16:56,840
Can you slap me awake?

185
00:16:56,920 --> 00:16:57,920
Of course.

186
00:16:59,000 --> 00:17:00,040
Did it hurt?

187
00:17:00,880 --> 00:17:02,080
- Did it hurt?
- Yeah.

188
00:17:02,600 --> 00:17:03,600
I'm not dreaming!

189
00:17:04,520 --> 00:17:05,640
I feel bad for Mook.

190
00:17:09,720 --> 00:17:12,480
Mook. Mook.

191
00:17:12,560 --> 00:17:15,880
Mook. Hold on.

192
00:17:28,840 --> 00:17:30,720
I'm tired of running away, Mom.

193
00:17:35,080 --> 00:17:36,600
I need to talk to him.

194
00:17:42,840 --> 00:17:44,880
Then, I'd better take Kongkwan to bed.

195
00:17:47,120 --> 00:17:48,080
Okay.

196
00:17:51,280 --> 00:17:52,200
Kongkwan,

197
00:17:53,360 --> 00:17:54,760
go to our room with Grandma.

198
00:17:55,760 --> 00:17:57,080
I need to talk to Thee first.

199
00:18:01,600 --> 00:18:04,760
Bye-bye, Thee. I have to go to bed now.

200
00:18:08,360 --> 00:18:09,440
Let's go, honey.

201
00:18:21,440 --> 00:18:24,120
How come you never told me
about your fiancée?

202
00:18:33,200 --> 00:18:34,360
I'm sorry.

203
00:18:36,760 --> 00:18:39,120
I didn't expect my mom to do this.

204
00:18:40,600 --> 00:18:42,240
But I did plan

205
00:18:42,960 --> 00:18:44,800
to straighten things out first,

206
00:18:45,880 --> 00:18:47,000
and then I'd tell you.

207
00:18:51,440 --> 00:18:52,720
But your mom did that

208
00:18:54,240 --> 00:18:56,520
to warn me to stay away from you.

209
00:18:57,480 --> 00:18:59,920
I won't allow it to go
according to my mom's plan!

210
00:19:00,000 --> 00:19:01,360
What about your fiancée?

211
00:19:03,040 --> 00:19:04,920
What can you do about that?

212
00:19:11,840 --> 00:19:12,920
I do believe…

213
00:19:15,440 --> 00:19:17,720
that you've been sincere with me.

214
00:19:22,560 --> 00:19:25,520
But I'm just not ready to face
the same problems again.

215
00:19:30,800 --> 00:19:34,080
Please just return
to your fiancée and your mom.

216
00:19:46,880 --> 00:19:48,040
I won't let you go.

217
00:20:01,560 --> 00:20:03,640
We need to accept the truth, Mr. Thee.

218
00:20:06,880 --> 00:20:08,240
Even if it hurts…

219
00:20:11,680 --> 00:20:13,440
we can't keep running away anymore.

220
00:20:18,520 --> 00:20:19,800
I won't give up!

221
00:20:27,400 --> 00:20:28,720
I really love you, Mook.

222
00:20:40,040 --> 00:20:42,200
<i>Kongkwan's really happy today.</i>

223
00:20:42,280 --> 00:20:44,000
<i>Thank you so much.</i>

224
00:20:44,080 --> 00:20:45,640
<i>I'm the one who should thank you.</i>

225
00:20:46,320 --> 00:20:48,320
<i>It's been a while</i>
<i>since I had a home-cooked meal.</i>

226
00:20:49,280 --> 00:20:52,080
<i>Your mom and Kongkwan are so sweet too.</i>

227
00:20:52,680 --> 00:20:54,440
Once I'm done handling things,

228
00:20:56,400 --> 00:20:59,120
I'll take you to meet my family too.

229
00:21:00,320 --> 00:21:02,800
<i>Why do I need to meet them?</i>

230
00:21:03,520 --> 00:21:06,360
<i>I just want to show off</i>
<i>my girlfriend to my family.</i>

231
00:21:06,880 --> 00:21:09,440
This is Bell, Thee's fiancée.

232
00:21:19,720 --> 00:21:20,600
Mook.

233
00:21:21,800 --> 00:21:22,800
Boss.

234
00:21:28,360 --> 00:21:30,000
What happened, Mook?

235
00:21:30,640 --> 00:21:31,520
Why are you crying?

236
00:21:31,600 --> 00:21:34,120
Mr. Thee has a fiancée.

237
00:21:35,080 --> 00:21:37,280
I made the wrong decision again.

238
00:21:52,600 --> 00:21:55,800
Do you know what you've done?

239
00:21:55,880 --> 00:21:58,480
I did what any mother should do.

240
00:21:59,200 --> 00:22:00,640
I told you, Thee,

241
00:22:01,240 --> 00:22:03,720
you'll have to marry Bell, no matter what.

242
00:22:05,360 --> 00:22:06,760
When it comes to work,

243
00:22:06,840 --> 00:22:09,960
I never got involved in your decisions.

244
00:22:10,760 --> 00:22:13,280
But this, I can't allow it,

245
00:22:13,800 --> 00:22:16,440
especially when that woman
already has a child.

246
00:22:21,120 --> 00:22:24,160
But Bell and I don't love
each other. You know that.

247
00:22:24,760 --> 00:22:25,840
It doesn't matter.

248
00:22:26,920 --> 00:22:29,000
What matters and has to happen

249
00:22:29,080 --> 00:22:32,080
is that you need to marry Bell.

250
00:22:33,120 --> 00:22:34,920
Everyone's agreed to it.

251
00:22:35,000 --> 00:22:38,680
We've agreed to plan a wedding
as soon as possible.

252
00:22:38,760 --> 00:22:41,280
I used to agree to it

253
00:22:41,360 --> 00:22:43,320
because I never thought
I could love someone,

254
00:22:43,400 --> 00:22:45,120
but then I met Mook.

255
00:22:46,880 --> 00:22:48,320
She made me realize

256
00:22:48,840 --> 00:22:50,840
that I must do everything
for the one I love.

257
00:22:52,400 --> 00:22:53,960
And I won't reluctantly do

258
00:22:55,000 --> 00:22:57,120
what I'll regret later.

259
00:23:03,840 --> 00:23:05,560
Do you really love that woman, Thee?

260
00:23:10,160 --> 00:23:13,880
I'm sorry, Bell. I really love her.

261
00:23:25,280 --> 00:23:26,160
Mom,

262
00:23:27,480 --> 00:23:30,040
stop trying to force our breakup

263
00:23:32,600 --> 00:23:34,080
because it'll never happen.

264
00:23:36,080 --> 00:23:37,720
Well, let's see who'll win!

265
00:23:38,960 --> 00:23:41,200
If you keep making stupid decisions,

266
00:23:41,280 --> 00:23:42,880
I won't go easy on you anymore.

267
00:23:44,560 --> 00:23:45,800
I built you up,

268
00:23:46,480 --> 00:23:48,400
but I can take you down too.

269
00:23:53,400 --> 00:23:56,440
Thee, come back here! Thee, come here!

270
00:23:56,520 --> 00:23:58,960
Uh, I'll talk to him for you.

271
00:24:11,800 --> 00:24:12,960
Aunt Anna,

272
00:24:13,680 --> 00:24:15,280
you should sit down and rest.

273
00:24:21,280 --> 00:24:25,280
He really went too far.
I've never seen him act this way.

274
00:24:30,320 --> 00:24:33,680
Bell, you won't leave him, right?

275
00:24:34,240 --> 00:24:36,120
You still love Thee, right?

276
00:24:49,160 --> 00:24:50,040
Mr. Thee.

277
00:24:54,000 --> 00:24:56,640
If you keep this up,

278
00:24:56,720 --> 00:24:59,080
you'll only make it harder for Ms. Mook.

279
00:25:01,160 --> 00:25:02,960
You know Mrs. Anna well.

280
00:25:03,560 --> 00:25:05,680
The more you care about Mook,

281
00:25:06,320 --> 00:25:08,880
the more she'll have to face trouble.

282
00:25:08,960 --> 00:25:10,840
But I have to explain myself to her!

283
00:25:11,640 --> 00:25:12,720
Tomorrow,

284
00:25:12,800 --> 00:25:15,720
Mrs. Anna is flying back to attend
an association event with Mr. John.

285
00:25:16,600 --> 00:25:18,280
Once she's back there,

286
00:25:18,880 --> 00:25:21,880
you can go meet Ms. Mook, okay?

287
00:25:24,440 --> 00:25:26,600
Please believe me, Mr. Thee.

288
00:25:29,280 --> 00:25:32,120
If you really want to fight for her,

289
00:25:32,640 --> 00:25:35,440
you have to be very patient.

290
00:25:44,800 --> 00:25:46,520
Please get some rest.

291
00:25:46,600 --> 00:25:48,440
As for your mom,

292
00:25:48,520 --> 00:25:51,800
I'll deal with her, so don't worry.

293
00:26:19,640 --> 00:26:20,840
Mom.

294
00:26:25,040 --> 00:26:26,920
Mom, I'm sorry.

295
00:26:28,760 --> 00:26:31,120
I made the wrong decision again, Mom.

296
00:26:36,360 --> 00:26:39,120
It's okay, honey. It's okay.

297
00:26:55,800 --> 00:26:57,200
Mrs. Anna left Thailand.

298
00:26:57,280 --> 00:26:59,200
She said she'd call you later.

299
00:27:07,000 --> 00:27:10,720
What are you going to do now, Thee?
Aunt Anna seemed really angry.

300
00:27:11,760 --> 00:27:14,040
I won't let her do as she pleases anymore.

301
00:27:15,800 --> 00:27:18,480
If I hadn't seen it for myself,
I wouldn't have believed

302
00:27:18,560 --> 00:27:21,160
that you're a guy
who can fall in love this hard.

303
00:27:24,880 --> 00:27:26,240
I really love her, Bell.

304
00:27:27,560 --> 00:27:29,160
And I'll do anything

305
00:27:29,240 --> 00:27:31,280
to show Mom that I really love her.

306
00:27:33,840 --> 00:27:36,800
I won't marry anyone

307
00:27:37,760 --> 00:27:40,360
other than Mook. You understand me, right?

308
00:27:41,560 --> 00:27:43,400
I'm not sure I understand

309
00:27:43,480 --> 00:27:45,960
because I don't believe in love
like you do.

310
00:27:47,000 --> 00:27:50,200
But as for our wedding,
I'll let you decide.

311
00:27:50,800 --> 00:27:53,680
I'm just using it as leverage
against my dad anyway.

312
00:27:54,200 --> 00:27:57,520
If you want to call it off,
I'm fine with that.

313
00:27:59,840 --> 00:28:01,600
Anyway, good luck.

314
00:28:12,480 --> 00:28:15,040
I'll get going then.
Mr. Pitak's driving me.

315
00:28:15,840 --> 00:28:16,760
Okay.

316
00:28:29,640 --> 00:28:32,560
Ms. Veluree and her friends
already checked out of the hotel.

317
00:28:33,840 --> 00:28:35,080
Thank you.

318
00:28:39,920 --> 00:28:41,760
MOOK

319
00:28:54,280 --> 00:28:57,240
Ms. Mook and her friends
already checked out this morning.

320
00:28:59,520 --> 00:29:01,960
Please give her some time.

321
00:29:02,040 --> 00:29:04,800
What she faced last night
was really serious.

322
00:29:05,960 --> 00:29:09,800
Thank you for your advice,
but I can deal with this myself.

323
00:29:21,240 --> 00:29:22,280
Thank you.

324
00:29:24,560 --> 00:29:28,160
Mook already went to work.
She said she had an important meeting.

325
00:29:29,920 --> 00:29:31,360
With everything that happened,

326
00:29:32,360 --> 00:29:33,640
I apologize, ma'am.

327
00:29:37,760 --> 00:29:40,320
You should apologize to Mook instead.

328
00:29:41,880 --> 00:29:44,640
But speaking as her mom,

329
00:29:45,400 --> 00:29:48,440
I don't want to see her
in that state again either.

330
00:29:49,800 --> 00:29:51,920
I'll make sure everything's sorted out.

331
00:29:52,000 --> 00:29:54,720
Even if you've dealt
with your fiancée situation,

332
00:29:54,800 --> 00:29:56,480
honestly,

333
00:29:57,320 --> 00:30:00,440
I don't think there's any way
you can deal with your mother.

334
00:30:01,120 --> 00:30:02,880
I've seen it time and time again,

335
00:30:02,960 --> 00:30:07,400
kids like you, who believe
love always wins.

336
00:30:08,320 --> 00:30:11,360
I'm serious about Mook. I really love her.

337
00:30:13,120 --> 00:30:15,120
I'll prove myself to you.

338
00:30:16,720 --> 00:30:18,520
If you can't keep your promise,

339
00:30:21,120 --> 00:30:22,760
please stop hurting Mook.

340
00:30:28,840 --> 00:30:30,440
You just had to be there.

341
00:30:30,520 --> 00:30:34,360
When Mr. Thee's mom showed up
to the party with his fiancée,

342
00:30:35,680 --> 00:30:38,120
there was this really intense energy.

343
00:30:38,200 --> 00:30:40,640
- I almost couldn't breathe.
- Whoa.

344
00:30:41,160 --> 00:30:42,760
So, how's Mook doing?

345
00:30:42,840 --> 00:30:45,160
She took Kongkwan
and her mom too, didn't she?

346
00:30:45,920 --> 00:30:49,280
I really feel bad for her.
It must've been a real shock.

347
00:30:50,560 --> 00:30:53,640
Oh, Mr. Thee, if you're already engaged,
why fool Mook?

348
00:30:55,360 --> 00:30:58,480
Aw, man. I got so happy
that she found a great boyfriend.

349
00:30:58,560 --> 00:31:00,960
Turns out he's even worse than her ex!

350
00:31:03,240 --> 00:31:05,080
What did Boss say?

351
00:31:06,440 --> 00:31:08,520
He was comforting her last night.

352
00:31:09,440 --> 00:31:12,000
But he's got to be so mad at Mr. Thee.

353
00:31:12,080 --> 00:31:15,440
Thank God they didn't meet last night,
otherwise it would've been…

354
00:31:17,360 --> 00:31:18,800
Would've been what?

355
00:31:18,880 --> 00:31:20,280
A mess, of course!

356
00:31:21,320 --> 00:31:22,160
Where's Ms. Mook?

357
00:31:28,040 --> 00:31:29,400
W-wait! Mr. Thee!

358
00:31:29,480 --> 00:31:32,560
- Mr. Thee!
- W-wait! Mr. Thee!

359
00:31:34,240 --> 00:31:35,080
Are you alright?

360
00:31:36,240 --> 00:31:37,120
Please go home and rest.

361
00:31:37,200 --> 00:31:38,760
I'll meet our client with Whan.

362
00:31:40,080 --> 00:31:41,320
I'm alright, Boss.

363
00:31:41,400 --> 00:31:43,320
I can separate my work and personal life.

364
00:31:45,680 --> 00:31:46,840
I'm worried about you, Mook.

365
00:31:48,320 --> 00:31:49,360
Don't push yourself.

366
00:31:50,440 --> 00:31:52,040
Mr. Thee! Mr. Thee!

367
00:31:52,120 --> 00:31:55,200
Please don't go in there, Mr. Thee!

368
00:31:55,280 --> 00:31:59,120
- Mr. Thee, please listen. Please.
- Mr. Thee!

369
00:31:59,200 --> 00:32:00,600
I need to talk to Mook urgently.

370
00:32:02,320 --> 00:32:03,800
I have nothing to say to you.

371
00:32:05,280 --> 00:32:06,200
Mook.

372
00:32:08,440 --> 00:32:09,760
Please listen to me.

373
00:32:11,280 --> 00:32:12,640
We need to talk this out.

374
00:32:16,320 --> 00:32:17,160
Mook.

375
00:32:20,000 --> 00:32:21,440
- Boss!
- Boss!

376
00:32:23,080 --> 00:32:26,240
You told me to compete with you, remember?

377
00:32:28,280 --> 00:32:31,320
Don't worry. I'm serious about Mook.

378
00:32:32,760 --> 00:32:36,840
So, if you also like her
and wish to compete with me,

379
00:32:36,920 --> 00:32:38,000
then by all means.

380
00:32:39,560 --> 00:32:40,560
But if not,

381
00:32:41,560 --> 00:32:43,080
get out of my way.

382
00:32:43,160 --> 00:32:45,040
<i>If you can't make Mook happy,</i>

383
00:32:45,720 --> 00:32:47,040
then get out of her life.

384
00:33:01,280 --> 00:33:02,080
Mook.

385
00:33:21,520 --> 00:33:28,400
<i>I want to scream and apologize to myself</i>
<i>For being too stupid</i>

386
00:33:29,040 --> 00:33:33,240
<i>It hurts so bad I could die</i>
<i>Yet I keep pushing myself…</i>

387
00:33:38,200 --> 00:33:40,960
Why is my life
so messed up right now, Boss?

388
00:33:42,840 --> 00:33:44,160
I understand

389
00:33:44,960 --> 00:33:47,240
that happiness can disappear so fast…

390
00:33:50,080 --> 00:33:52,000
but isn't this a bit too fast?

391
00:33:54,840 --> 00:33:56,360
That's just how life is.

392
00:33:57,840 --> 00:34:01,200
You can never predict
what will happen to you.

393
00:34:10,199 --> 00:34:11,400
I think…

394
00:34:15,159 --> 00:34:17,440
I'd better stay
as far away from him as I can.

395
00:34:19,480 --> 00:34:23,280
No talking, no meeting, no contact.

396
00:34:24,800 --> 00:34:27,199
Maybe it'll help me move on more easily.

397
00:34:38,360 --> 00:34:39,679
Don't worry about that.

398
00:34:40,960 --> 00:34:42,360
I'll talk to Mr. Thee.

399
00:34:45,480 --> 00:34:46,880
Thank you, Boss.

400
00:34:53,880 --> 00:34:55,440
MR. PITAK

401
00:35:04,640 --> 00:35:05,680
Thank you.

402
00:35:10,200 --> 00:35:11,320
Good afternoon.

403
00:35:15,440 --> 00:35:17,240
I'm sorry, Ms. Mook.

404
00:35:17,320 --> 00:35:19,040
I'm just doing my job.

405
00:35:20,360 --> 00:35:21,560
I understand.

406
00:35:22,840 --> 00:35:24,280
Good luck, Ms. Mook.

407
00:35:27,800 --> 00:35:28,640
Have a seat.

408
00:35:49,560 --> 00:35:52,080
Thank you for meeting with me.

409
00:35:53,360 --> 00:35:55,240
Let me just get to the point,

410
00:35:56,240 --> 00:35:58,320
so I won't keep you for too long.

411
00:36:00,200 --> 00:36:01,280
Sure.

412
00:36:02,000 --> 00:36:05,520
You know Thee's got
a bright future ahead of him,

413
00:36:06,680 --> 00:36:09,480
and I've found a perfect partner for him.

414
00:36:14,760 --> 00:36:16,280
I don't mean to disrespect you,

415
00:36:17,360 --> 00:36:20,320
but you've been married before,

416
00:36:20,920 --> 00:36:22,640
and you're divorced at such a young age.

417
00:36:23,160 --> 00:36:26,040
You're quite talented at your job,

418
00:36:27,360 --> 00:36:28,520
but to me,

419
00:36:29,360 --> 00:36:30,840
it's nothing special.

420
00:36:32,920 --> 00:36:36,360
Plus, I don't see any way
you can support Thee

421
00:36:36,440 --> 00:36:38,440
to help him succeed in life.

422
00:36:40,760 --> 00:36:42,560
I'm sure you understand
how a mother feels.

423
00:36:44,080 --> 00:36:46,000
Mothers like us always want

424
00:36:46,080 --> 00:36:48,520
what's best for our children.

425
00:36:53,160 --> 00:36:54,360
No, I don't understand.

426
00:36:57,440 --> 00:37:00,040
I don't understand
why you look down on others

427
00:37:00,920 --> 00:37:03,320
and only see your son's worth.

428
00:37:06,320 --> 00:37:08,240
If I have to break up with Mr. Thee,

429
00:37:09,280 --> 00:37:11,200
it's only because I can't stand having

430
00:37:11,720 --> 00:37:13,600
a boyfriend whose mom behaves this way,

431
00:37:15,480 --> 00:37:17,480
not because I'm divorced

432
00:37:18,000 --> 00:37:20,320
or because I don't have
an outstanding career.

433
00:37:23,000 --> 00:37:24,480
But don't worry,

434
00:37:25,200 --> 00:37:28,040
because I have to choose
what's best for me too.

435
00:37:30,160 --> 00:37:33,280
Hopefully, we won't have to waste time
discussing this again.

436
00:37:56,600 --> 00:37:57,640
<i>Is something the matter?</i>

437
00:37:57,720 --> 00:38:00,480
I'd like to handle
The One's project in place of Mook

438
00:38:01,280 --> 00:38:03,160
because Mook is no longer comfortable

439
00:38:03,880 --> 00:38:05,400
to meet you like before.

440
00:38:06,400 --> 00:38:07,280
I won't allow it.

441
00:38:08,240 --> 00:38:10,080
She has to continue handling it.

442
00:38:11,560 --> 00:38:13,240
Please don't do this, Mr. Thee.

443
00:38:13,320 --> 00:38:15,560
Don't use work as an excuse

444
00:38:15,640 --> 00:38:18,240
when you can't even protect her.

445
00:38:18,920 --> 00:38:21,800
You're not even in a state
where you can protect her.

446
00:38:22,920 --> 00:38:24,240
Please let her go.

447
00:38:27,360 --> 00:38:28,160
Mr. Anapat.

448
00:38:29,560 --> 00:38:32,040
I suggest you take another look
at our contract,

449
00:38:32,120 --> 00:38:34,200
because what you're trying to do

450
00:38:34,720 --> 00:38:36,760
will affect the contract we signed.

451
00:38:52,480 --> 00:38:54,040
How's Mook doing, Boss?

452
00:38:54,640 --> 00:38:56,200
She's still devastated.

453
00:38:57,240 --> 00:38:58,520
She'll need more time.

454
00:39:01,360 --> 00:39:02,680
As for her work,

455
00:39:02,760 --> 00:39:04,400
I've talked to Mr. Thee.

456
00:39:08,120 --> 00:39:09,640
We'll continue our project,

457
00:39:10,240 --> 00:39:12,280
but I'll handle it in place of Mook.

458
00:39:13,640 --> 00:39:15,200
But in the contract,

459
00:39:15,280 --> 00:39:18,240
it clearly specifies
that Mook has to be in charge.

460
00:39:18,960 --> 00:39:21,600
Won't this cause an issue, Boss?

461
00:39:23,120 --> 00:39:24,760
If that's what the contract says,

462
00:39:25,720 --> 00:39:27,800
I'll keep being in charge until it ends.

463
00:39:27,880 --> 00:39:28,920
Mook.

464
00:39:30,240 --> 00:39:33,480
I'll show them
that we're only where we're at

465
00:39:33,560 --> 00:39:35,520
because we're professional enough.

466
00:39:39,400 --> 00:39:42,520
- Are you fine with meeting Mr. Thee?
- Yeah!

467
00:39:43,880 --> 00:39:47,360
Sooner or later, I'll have to move on.
It's no big deal.

468
00:39:50,000 --> 00:39:51,800
Mook, you rock!

469
00:40:30,800 --> 00:40:31,640
Stop.

470
00:40:33,640 --> 00:40:35,280
Please keep a distance between us.

471
00:40:41,320 --> 00:40:44,120
- Mook.
- Stop trying. It's pointless,

472
00:40:45,880 --> 00:40:47,760
because every time you step closer,

473
00:40:49,400 --> 00:40:51,560
I'll keep stepping further away.

474
00:40:52,240 --> 00:40:53,200
I'm really sorry

475
00:40:53,800 --> 00:40:55,000
about what happened.

476
00:40:56,320 --> 00:40:58,280
I never meant to hide it from you, Mook.

477
00:41:01,400 --> 00:41:03,520
I just wanted to solve the problem first

478
00:41:03,600 --> 00:41:05,160
before telling you.

479
00:41:08,040 --> 00:41:09,280
Which problem?

480
00:41:09,960 --> 00:41:11,280
Your fiancée

481
00:41:12,000 --> 00:41:13,000
or your mom?

482
00:41:20,240 --> 00:41:23,120
Mr. Pitak told me
my mom spoke with you today.

483
00:41:24,720 --> 00:41:25,760
Are you okay?

484
00:41:28,520 --> 00:41:29,440
I'm pretty good.

485
00:41:30,920 --> 00:41:32,400
Your mom's quite straightforward.

486
00:41:34,720 --> 00:41:36,360
She keeps things simple.

487
00:41:37,240 --> 00:41:38,560
She made it very clear

488
00:41:40,840 --> 00:41:41,800
that there should be

489
00:41:43,440 --> 00:41:45,320
a distance between us.

490
00:41:49,200 --> 00:41:50,840
But don't worry about our work.

491
00:41:52,080 --> 00:41:53,640
I can separate my personal life…

492
00:41:56,360 --> 00:41:57,360
or rather,

493
00:41:58,680 --> 00:42:00,680
nonsense, and my work.

494
00:42:06,600 --> 00:42:09,560
- Mook, listen to me--
- You should do the same.

495
00:42:11,600 --> 00:42:12,880
To start with,

496
00:42:15,400 --> 00:42:16,680
stop coming here.

497
00:42:18,720 --> 00:42:20,240
This has nothing to do with work.

498
00:42:24,120 --> 00:42:25,400
If you'll excuse me.

499
00:43:04,200 --> 00:43:06,280
You've talked to Mr. Thee, right?

500
00:43:07,800 --> 00:43:10,800
He was parked there waiting for you
since early in the evening.

501
00:43:14,600 --> 00:43:15,520
Yes.

502
00:43:22,600 --> 00:43:24,000
Don't worry, Mom.

503
00:43:26,600 --> 00:43:28,040
I can get through this.

504
00:44:04,400 --> 00:44:05,240
What's up, Ploy?

505
00:44:05,320 --> 00:44:08,120
I have the evidence
to hold Top accountable now.

506
00:44:11,000 --> 00:44:11,840
Are you sure?

507
00:44:11,920 --> 00:44:13,520
Yes,

508
00:44:13,600 --> 00:44:16,320
but I'm worried that it won't be enough.

509
00:44:18,080 --> 00:44:20,240
Send me all of his information.

510
00:44:20,760 --> 00:44:22,560
I think I know how to deal with him.

511
00:45:31,040 --> 00:45:32,040
<i>Take a look at this.</i>

512
00:45:32,120 --> 00:45:34,360
Is this your oh-so-nice friend?

513
00:46:08,200 --> 00:46:09,560
- Excuse me, Mook.
- Come in.

514
00:46:11,880 --> 00:46:14,520
- Here's your coffee. Careful, it's hot.
- Okay.

515
00:46:14,600 --> 00:46:15,800
Is Boss here yet?

516
00:46:15,880 --> 00:46:17,280
He won't be here this morning.

517
00:46:17,360 --> 00:46:19,200
He said he's going to a party at The One.

518
00:46:19,880 --> 00:46:21,920
What party? Why haven't
I heard about this?

519
00:46:24,760 --> 00:46:26,640
It's a welcome party
for Mr. Thee's fiancée.

520
00:46:28,520 --> 00:46:31,120
We were invited too, but Boss told us

521
00:46:31,200 --> 00:46:32,760
not to tell you.

522
00:46:37,000 --> 00:46:38,080
Hold on, Whan.

523
00:46:38,920 --> 00:46:39,760
Yes?

524
00:46:39,840 --> 00:46:41,440
Call an urgent meeting.

525
00:46:41,520 --> 00:46:43,120
I have a new project for our team.

526
00:46:47,520 --> 00:46:49,560
Why didn't you tell me
before hosting an event?

527
00:46:49,640 --> 00:46:52,000
Why'd you need to host this party
and make a big fuss?

528
00:46:52,080 --> 00:46:53,560
Well, Mr. Joe

529
00:46:53,640 --> 00:46:57,440
is about to sign a contract
for a megaproject with TJ Group.

530
00:46:58,000 --> 00:47:00,280
He wants some certainty from us.

531
00:47:01,280 --> 00:47:02,520
I'm sure you know

532
00:47:02,600 --> 00:47:04,200
that signing this contract

533
00:47:04,280 --> 00:47:06,720
will greatly increase our company's stock.

534
00:47:07,480 --> 00:47:10,800
But we could've just announced
the signing and the project details.

535
00:47:10,880 --> 00:47:12,760
What if they ask about you and Bell?

536
00:47:12,840 --> 00:47:14,280
What do I tell them?

537
00:47:14,800 --> 00:47:18,360
Don't you fall in love so hard
that it affects TJ Group.

538
00:47:19,080 --> 00:47:20,960
Please cooperate with me.

539
00:47:21,480 --> 00:47:23,440
You just need to stand there and smile.

540
00:47:23,960 --> 00:47:25,920
I'll handle everything else.

541
00:47:56,000 --> 00:47:57,080
What?

542
00:48:09,600 --> 00:48:11,080
Do you not know how to drive?

543
00:48:12,040 --> 00:48:12,920
Hey.

544
00:48:13,000 --> 00:48:14,320
It's you again?

545
00:48:15,000 --> 00:48:15,960
Thank God it's you.

546
00:48:16,040 --> 00:48:18,160
I'm really late, and I'm in a big rush.

547
00:48:18,240 --> 00:48:20,440
Would you mind parking my car for me?

548
00:48:20,520 --> 00:48:21,840
I'm not very good at it.

549
00:48:22,920 --> 00:48:24,440
Call me when you're done.

550
00:48:24,520 --> 00:48:25,800
I'll be at the party at this hotel.

551
00:48:26,520 --> 00:48:27,960
Bye. Please do it for me.

552
00:48:47,760 --> 00:48:49,840
- May I take a picture?
- Sure.

553
00:48:50,360 --> 00:48:51,440
Move closer, please.

554
00:48:52,600 --> 00:48:53,440
‪Perfect.

555
00:48:57,240 --> 00:48:58,840
- Good.
- Thank you very much.

556
00:48:59,800 --> 00:49:03,880
- Thank you very much for coming today.
- Of course.

557
00:49:05,440 --> 00:49:07,400
- My pleasure.
- Hello, Mrs. Anna.

558
00:49:09,480 --> 00:49:11,040
Hello, Mr. Joe.

559
00:49:11,960 --> 00:49:13,880
Welcome to The One.

560
00:49:15,120 --> 00:49:18,120
Thank you for hosting
this welcome party for my daughter.

561
00:49:19,880 --> 00:49:21,800
It's to celebrate our success.

562
00:49:28,880 --> 00:49:30,080
To catch a criminal?!

563
00:49:30,680 --> 00:49:32,960
Yes, and we must make no mistakes.

564
00:49:33,480 --> 00:49:35,720
We need to catch him
successfully in one go.

565
00:49:36,360 --> 00:49:38,760
How are we going to do that, Mook?
Who is he?

566
00:49:46,600 --> 00:49:49,520
He seems so nice and polite.

567
00:49:49,600 --> 00:49:52,920
If you didn't tell me,
I'd never take him for a bad guy.

568
00:49:55,240 --> 00:49:56,400
He's my husband.

569
00:49:56,480 --> 00:49:58,320
Ploy, have a seat.

570
00:49:59,560 --> 00:50:02,120
- Please have a seat.
- Thank you.

571
00:50:02,200 --> 00:50:03,880
This is Ploy, my best friend.

572
00:50:05,040 --> 00:50:05,880
Hello.

573
00:50:11,520 --> 00:50:13,720
His name is Top.

574
00:50:14,240 --> 00:50:16,400
On the outside, he seems nice

575
00:50:16,480 --> 00:50:18,040
and polite.

576
00:50:18,120 --> 00:50:20,600
He likes to make merit and help people.

577
00:50:20,680 --> 00:50:21,840
PIAMSUK ORPHANAGE

578
00:50:21,920 --> 00:50:24,680
But he has another side
no one knows about.

579
00:50:25,320 --> 00:50:27,160
A dark side, if you will.

580
00:50:27,240 --> 00:50:30,000
You see, he likes to get close to women

581
00:50:30,080 --> 00:50:33,080
and when they agree to sleep with him,

582
00:50:33,600 --> 00:50:35,960
he'd secretly film them to blackmail them.

583
00:50:41,240 --> 00:50:43,160
And even worse,

584
00:50:45,120 --> 00:50:48,240
he likes to beat women.

585
00:50:52,440 --> 00:50:54,680
I can confirm it

586
00:50:56,480 --> 00:50:58,520
because I've faced it first-hand.

587
00:50:58,600 --> 00:51:01,320
If he did all this,
why didn't you go to the police?

588
00:51:02,120 --> 00:51:03,480
I did.

589
00:51:04,960 --> 00:51:08,200
But I don't have proof
that he filmed those videos.

590
00:51:10,720 --> 00:51:13,840
Plus, if I just wait
for the police to handle it,

591
00:51:14,720 --> 00:51:16,720
I'm scared he'll catch on to me

592
00:51:16,800 --> 00:51:18,480
and destroy the evidence.

593
00:51:19,000 --> 00:51:20,840
Then he'll never be arrested for sure.

594
00:51:43,640 --> 00:51:45,080
MOOK

595
00:51:54,520 --> 00:51:56,040
It's time, Mr. Thee.

596
00:51:56,120 --> 00:51:57,200
Ms. Bella's arrived.

597
00:52:00,120 --> 00:52:02,440
Do I really need to do this, Mr. Pitak?

598
00:52:02,520 --> 00:52:04,880
I'm sure you were prepared
for this to happen.

599
00:52:05,720 --> 00:52:08,000
Mrs. Anna won't back down so easily.

600
00:52:08,720 --> 00:52:10,200
I won't either.

601
00:52:27,440 --> 00:52:29,480
We didn't really have to come.

602
00:52:29,560 --> 00:52:32,200
Our company's got nothing
to do with The One.

603
00:52:32,280 --> 00:52:34,320
I just wanted to see it with my own eyes,

604
00:52:34,840 --> 00:52:36,800
the kind of face she'll make when she sees

605
00:52:37,320 --> 00:52:38,280
his actual girlfriend.

606
00:52:48,360 --> 00:52:49,200
Mr. Pat.

607
00:52:50,520 --> 00:52:51,920
I can't get hold of Mook.

608
00:52:52,440 --> 00:52:53,920
Do you know where she is?

609
00:52:55,120 --> 00:52:55,960
No, I don't.

610
00:53:07,160 --> 00:53:09,960
Hello, ladies and gentlemen.

611
00:53:10,040 --> 00:53:12,360
First of all, TJ Group

612
00:53:12,440 --> 00:53:14,880
would like to thank you all

613
00:53:15,480 --> 00:53:19,480
for taking the time
to come to our party today.

614
00:53:21,520 --> 00:53:24,440
Today, I wanted to host a humble party

615
00:53:24,520 --> 00:53:28,400
to welcome Thee's bride-to-be.

616
00:53:29,040 --> 00:53:30,120
‪Who?

617
00:53:34,600 --> 00:53:38,440
Without further ado,
I'd like to introduce you

618
00:53:39,120 --> 00:53:42,240
to Bella, Thee's fiancée!

619
00:53:52,880 --> 00:53:57,480
But before, you told the press
that you were dating Ms. Veluree.

620
00:54:00,240 --> 00:54:02,720
There's been a little misunderstanding.

621
00:54:02,800 --> 00:54:05,280
So we hosted this party today

622
00:54:05,360 --> 00:54:09,400
to provide the press
with accurate information,

623
00:54:09,920 --> 00:54:11,040
which is that Bell

624
00:54:11,120 --> 00:54:14,880
is the fiancée of Mr. Thee,
an executive at TJ Group.

625
00:54:15,560 --> 00:54:17,320
We're also about to have great news

626
00:54:17,400 --> 00:54:20,000
to share with you all very soon.

627
00:54:26,640 --> 00:54:28,960
- Actually--
- Our families

628
00:54:29,040 --> 00:54:31,480
are co-investing in a megaproject.

629
00:54:32,080 --> 00:54:36,560
And I assure you, it's a project
that'll make everyone go, "Wow."

630
00:54:37,880 --> 00:54:40,600
Please give a big hand
to Mr. Joe, an executive

631
00:54:40,680 --> 00:54:44,720
of Victoria Industry Group
and also an important partner of ours!

632
00:54:57,640 --> 00:55:00,360
- This camera, please.
- Thank you.

633
00:55:01,600 --> 00:55:02,800
- This camera too.
- Perfect.

634
00:55:02,880 --> 00:55:04,960
- One more, please.
- Thank you.

635
00:55:05,040 --> 00:55:08,200
‪-Good!
‪-One more, please.

636
00:55:08,280 --> 00:55:09,560
‪Perfect!

637
00:55:09,640 --> 00:55:11,040
- This camera too.
- Smile, please.

638
00:55:11,120 --> 00:55:13,880
- Perfect.
- Thank you.

639
00:55:26,480 --> 00:55:27,600
Sorry.

640
00:55:27,680 --> 00:55:31,120
You never called me, but I saw you
back there, so I waited here for you.

641
00:55:37,040 --> 00:55:39,080
Hey. My car key, please?

642
00:55:44,440 --> 00:55:46,440
Thank you. You saved me again.

643
00:56:15,800 --> 00:56:18,880
I didn't know you were Mr. Thee's fiancée.

644
00:56:19,800 --> 00:56:20,640
And?

645
00:56:21,960 --> 00:56:24,080
Why'd you have to hide from his mom?

646
00:56:25,040 --> 00:56:26,600
Well, it's enough family time for now.

647
00:56:26,680 --> 00:56:28,520
I have things to do.

648
00:56:32,880 --> 00:56:33,880
Wait!

649
00:56:39,400 --> 00:56:40,440
Here.

650
00:56:41,920 --> 00:56:43,160
Do you know this address?

651
00:56:43,240 --> 00:56:45,520
I'm not quite familiar
with the roads in Thailand.

652
00:56:55,680 --> 00:56:56,880
{\an8}Now you're asking for it!

653
00:56:58,640 --> 00:57:00,920
{\an8}‪-Let go!
‪-Ploy, stop! Don't help me!

654
00:57:01,680 --> 00:57:02,520
{\an8}Let go!

655
00:57:05,640 --> 00:57:06,680
{\an8}Let go!

656
00:57:07,760 --> 00:57:10,160
{\an8}How come you got here
with Mr. Pat last night?

657
00:57:10,960 --> 00:57:12,280
{\an8}It's a long story, Thee.

658
00:57:13,320 --> 00:57:16,880
{\an8}Yesterday I saw Mr. Anapat and Mook.
They seemed really close.

659
00:57:17,680 --> 00:57:19,360
{\an8}Does he have a crush on her too?

660
00:57:19,440 --> 00:57:21,120
{\an8}I'm really worried about you.

661
00:57:21,640 --> 00:57:23,640
{\an8}Don't risk your life like that again.

662
00:57:25,200 --> 00:57:28,560
{\an8}I wouldn't know what to do if something
were to happen to you.

663
00:58:28,000 --> 00:58:30,120
{\an8}Subtitle translation by:
Ramil Natnitiwitaya

